    <section name="Installation">
     
      <p>The installation of Aozan on all *nix systems is quite similar and very easy. You don't need to be the root user of your system to install Aozan.</p> 
     
      <p>The only tool you need to have is a tar/gz/bz2/zip extractor.</p>
     
      <ul>
        <li><a href="download.html">Download Aozan</a> on our website.</li>

		<source>$ wget @@@WEBSITE@@@/aozan-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.gz</source>

        <li>Unzip the archive where you want install the software.</li>

		<source>$ tar xzf aozan-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.gz</source>

        <li>Aozan is ready to run.</li>
      
        <li>You can now launch Aozan manually:</li> 
<source>$ cd aozan-@@@VERSION@@@
$ ./aozan.sh /etc/aozan.conf</source>
				
        <li><p>Or as cron job, see <a href="quickstart.html#aozan_cron_job">details here.</a></p></li>
	</ul>

		<!-- 
      	<p>If you want to run Aozan on a local Hadoop cluster, see the <a href="hadoopmode.html">Hadoop configuration page</a> for more information about Hadoop installation and configuration.</p>
      	-->

   </section>
   
